The notion of Being] or even of substance in general, apart from this or that special combination of attributes, and that of a combination so complex as to admit of no additional attributes in thought, are both psychologically inconceivable. A Highest Genus and a Lowest Species may be admitted in any material science, as the limits at which the investigations of that science begin and end 3 but such a limitation is made entirely on material grounds, relatively to the purpose of that par— ticular science, and cannot be recognised by Logic.
